===Alternative forms===
* In mainland China and Japan, the character is composed of {{l|mul|冫}} and {{l|mul|熈}} as the right and left components.
* In Taiwan and Hong Kong, only the upper left component consists of {{l|mul|冫}} while the bottom consists entirely of {{l|mul|灬}}.
* In Korea, the middle component {{l|mul|丿}} is missing and {{l|mul|巳}} is replaced by {{l|mul|㔾}}. <!-- Refer Unicode charts, version 10.0 (2017) -->
* A CJK compatibility ideograph exists at <code>U+FA15</code> which is similar to the Korean form except {{l|mul|㔾}} is replaced by {{l|mul|巳}}.

